headline.main: CONGRESS TIES UP WAR AGENCY FUNDS; Votes 71 1/2 Billion Army Bill but Is Unable to Resolve Its Disputes Over Others

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, June 30 -- Continued disagreements between the Senate and the House blocked the attempts of Congress tonight to drive through to final enactment a half-dozen log-jammed appropriation bills, containing a total of more than $5,300,000,000 of funds required by war agencies and other governmental establishments to meet obligations of the fiscal year which starts at midnight.
abstract: Grade labeling: Sen sustains House ban
